	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town - A man has burnt to death and three others have
been left injured after the car they were travelling in crashed down a cliff, the
Western Cape traffic department said on Wednesday. "Allegedly occupants were travelling from Gordon's Bay
in the direction of Rooi Els. The driver lost control and went down the cliff.
The motor vehicle caught alight," said provincial traffic chief Kenny
Africa. One male passenger burned to death, while the three other
occupants were slightly injured. The accident occurred on the R44 before Kogel Bay at around 02:30. Police are investigating the crash. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  